olive oil
1 radish
1 cucumber
1 packet Crumbed Chicken Breast Strips
1 sachet barbecue seasoning
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
1 packet Corn Chips
1 packet sour cream
1 bag coriander
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Roughly chop tomato
• Thinly slice cucumber
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks

• To a bowl, add mayonnaise
• To a second bowl, add panko
breadcrumbs and seasoning
• Toss chicken in mayo, then
breadcrumbs
• Heat a generous drizzle of olive oil in
a frying pan over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken, tossing, until golden
and cooked through, 5-6 mins

• In a large bowl, combine chicken,
tomato, cucumber, mixed salad
leaves, chipotle sauce and a drizzle
of oil. Season
• Plate up salad. Crumble over corn
chips and sprinkle with Cheddar
• Serve with sour cream and
torn coriander